# Announcement Page Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Create a new `announcement.html` page based on [template.html](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/template.html), styled similarly to [search.html](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/search.html) (per user request). The page will display the full text of an announcement or news item.

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] `announcement.html`
- Create from [template.html](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/template.html).
- Add [assets/css/search.css](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/assets/css/search.css) and a new `assets/css/announcement.css` to the `<head>`.
- In the `<main>` area, replace the placeholder with the actual announcement content container.
- Use styling patterns from [search.html](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/search.html): a title box with background (`#f5f5f5`) and a content area.
- Structure the content with:
  - Announcement Title (e.g., `<h1>`, styled like `.search-title-box` or similar header).
  - Date and Source/Badge.
  - Full WYSIWYG/rich-text content area.
  - "Back to Previous" or "Back to Home" button.

### [NEW] `assets/css/announcement.css`
- Specific styles for the announcement content formatting (line-height, paragraph spacing, image max-width).
- Re-use or extend classes from [search.css](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/assets/css/search.css) for visual consistency.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- View `announcement.html` in the browser.
- Check desktop and mobile responsiveness (using browser dev tools).
- Verify colors, fonts, and spacing align with [search.html](file:///d:/laragon/www/hki/search.html) and the overall design system.
